window.DOCS_SEARCH=[{"t":"What is Stockwik?","u":"/docs/getting-started/what-is-stockwik.html","s":"Getting started","d":"Stockwik is inventory and replenishment software for Shopify merchants who fulfill from a single hub. It learns how your products actually sell and tells you exactly what to reorde","k":"Who it's for The core loop What makes it different What's next Related"},{"t":"Installing Stockwik","u":"/docs/getting-started/installing.html","s":"Getting started","d":"Stockwik installs from the Shopify App Store and connects to your store in a few clicks. Here's what to expect.","k":"Install from Shopify What Stockwik can access After installing Related"},{"t":"Choosing a plan","u":"/docs/getting-started/choosing-a-plan.html","s":"Getting started","d":"Right after you install, Stockwik asks you to pick a plan. Every plan starts with a 14-day free trial, and all billing is handled securely through Shopify.","k":"The three plans How it works Related"},{"t":"Creating your account","u":"/docs/getting-started/creating-your-account.html","s":"Getting started","d":"After you've chosen a plan, you'll create your Stockwik account. Most of the form is already filled in from your Shopify store, so it only takes a moment.","k":"Sign up Verify your email Your workspace Related"},{"t":"The onboarding walkthrough","u":"/docs/getting-started/onboarding-walkthrough.html","s":"Getting started","d":"The first time you open Stockwik, a setup wizard walks you through connecting your store and getting your planning data in shape. It takes just a few minutes, and most steps are op","k":"Step 1 — Connect Step 2 — Import Step 3 — Suppliers (optional) Step 4 — Planning defaults Step 5 — Product costs (optional) Step 6 — Buy options (optional) Step 7 — Finish Related"},{"t":"Dashboard tour","u":"/docs/getting-started/dashboard-tour.html","s":"Getting started","d":"Once you've finished setup, you land on your dashboard. Here's a quick tour of how Stockwik is laid out.","k":"The left navigation The Home overview The Sync button Your account menu Related"},{"t":"Inventory: on hand, available & committed","u":"/docs/concepts/inventory-on-hand-available-committed.html","s":"Core concepts","d":"Stockwik mirrors four inventory numbers from Shopify for every product. Knowing what each one means is the key to reading the rest of the app — especially the reorder suggestions, ","k":"The four numbers A quick example Why \"available\" is what matters for planning Where you'll see these numbers Related"},{"t":"How sales velocity works","u":"/docs/concepts/how-sales-velocity-works.html","s":"Core concepts","d":"\"Velocity\" is just how fast a product sells. It's the engine behind every reorder suggestion: it decides when a product needs reordering and how much to buy. Stockwik calculates it","k":"Blended velocity (your normal pace) Peak velocity (your busy stretch) Seasonal products What feeds velocity Related"},{"t":"How reorder levels are calculated","u":"/docs/concepts/how-reorder-levels-are-calculated.html","s":"Core concepts","d":"Stockwik answers three questions for every product: when to reorder, how much to order, and how urgent it is. It does this from your real sales history — no guessing, no spreadshee","k":"The reorder point (minimum) The order-up-to level (maximum) A worked example How the suggested order quantity is figured Seasonal products When you want to override the math What the statuses mean Related"},{"t":"Planning defaults & overrides","u":"/docs/concepts/planning-defaults-and-overrides.html","s":"Core concepts","d":"Stockwik uses a few planning levers to calculate your reorder levels. You set sensible defaults once for your whole store, then override them on individual products where it makes ","k":"Organization defaults Per-product overrides Bulk editing via CSV Related"},{"t":"ABC classification","u":"/docs/concepts/abc-classification.html","s":"Core concepts","d":"ABC classification ranks your products by how much revenue they bring in, so you can focus your attention where it matters most. Stockwik calculates it automatically and shows a co","k":"How it works Why it's useful Related"},{"t":"Buy options & pack sizes","u":"/docs/concepts/buy-options-and-pack-sizes.html","s":"Core concepts","d":"You count stock in single units, but you often buy in cases, boxes, or pallets. A buy option is how Stockwik bridges the two — it describes one way you purchase a product from a su","k":"What a buy option includes Why units-per-pack matters Multiple options per product Where to manage them Related"},{"t":"How syncing works","u":"/docs/concepts/how-syncing-works.html","s":"Core concepts","d":"Stockwik mirrors your Shopify store. Syncing is how it pulls the latest data in — and Shopify always stays the source of truth for your stock.","k":"What a sync pulls Shopify is the source of truth What happens on your first sync When to sync Related"},{"t":"Glossary","u":"/docs/concepts/glossary.html","s":"Core concepts","d":"Quick definitions of the terms you'll see across Stockwik.","k":"Related"},{"t":"Inventory list & views","u":"/docs/inventory/inventory-list-and-views.html","s":"Inventory","d":"The Inventory page is your product catalog, mirrored from Shopify and enriched with planning data. It has several views that slice your products by what needs attention.","k":"The views Reading the columns Finding and organizing products The Actions menu Related"},{"t":"Product detail","u":"/docs/inventory/product-detail.html","s":"Inventory","d":"Click any product name (from Inventory, Reorder, or anywhere it's linked) to open its detail page — the full picture for one product, and where you fine-tune how it's planned and p","k":"At the top Pricing & inventory Demand & planning Replenishment rules tab Suppliers tab Related"},{"t":"Import & export inventory","u":"/docs/inventory/import-export-inventory.html","s":"Inventory","d":"For bulk changes, Stockwik lets you export your products to a spreadsheet, edit them, and re-import. It's the fastest way to set costs and planning overrides across many products a","k":"Exporting What you can import Override syntax The import flow Related"},{"t":"Managing suppliers","u":"/docs/suppliers/managing-suppliers.html","s":"Suppliers","d":"Suppliers are who you buy from. Their details — especially lead time — feed directly into your reorder timing and appear on the purchase orders you send.","k":"The suppliers list Supplier details Seeding suppliers from Shopify Buy options & POs on a supplier Related"},{"t":"Buy options","u":"/docs/suppliers/buy-options.html","s":"Suppliers","d":"A buy option is one way you purchase a product from a supplier — its pack size, cost, and minimum order. (For the concept and why units-per-pack matters, see Buy options & pack siz","k":"Where to manage buy options Adding a buy option Related"},{"t":"Suppliers & buy options import/export","u":"/docs/suppliers/import-export.html","s":"Suppliers","d":"Both suppliers and buy options support spreadsheet import/export, so you can set up or update many at once. Both follow the same safe preview → apply flow as the rest of Stockwik.","k":"Suppliers Buy options The shared flow Related"},{"t":"The Reorder page","u":"/docs/reordering/the-reorder-page.html","s":"Reordering","d":"The Reorder page is where Stockwik earns its keep: a live buy list that tells you what to order right now, how much, and from whom — grouped by supplier and ready to turn into purc","k":"Status summary Controls Grouped by supplier Turning it into orders Related"},{"t":"Understanding suggestions","u":"/docs/reordering/understanding-suggestions.html","s":"Reordering","d":"The Need column on the Reorder page is Stockwik's suggested order quantity. Here's exactly how it's worked out, so you know when to trust it and when to adjust.","k":"How the suggested quantity is calculated Why some items suggest 0 On-order awareness When you've pinned an override Adjusting before you order Related"},{"t":"Create POs from suggestions","u":"/docs/reordering/create-pos-from-suggestions.html","s":"Reordering","d":"The fastest way to raise purchase orders is straight from your reorder list. Select what you want, and Stockwik drafts the POs for you — grouped by supplier.","k":"Steps What gets carried over Related"},{"t":"Creating & editing purchase orders","u":"/docs/purchase-orders/creating-and-editing-pos.html","s":"Purchase orders","d":"Purchase orders (POs) are how you order stock from suppliers. You can create them automatically from your reorder list or build one by hand, then edit freely while they're still dr","k":"Two ways to create a PO What's on a PO The PO lifecycle Editing Related"},{"t":"Sending a purchase order","u":"/docs/purchase-orders/sending-a-po.html","s":"Purchase orders","d":"When a draft PO is ready, you mark it as ordered and get it to your supplier — by email, print, or your own channel.","k":"Mark it ordered Get it to the supplier What the supplier sees Related"},{"t":"Receiving stock","u":"/docs/purchase-orders/receiving-stock.html","s":"Purchase orders","d":"When a shipment arrives, receive it against its purchase order. Stockwik updates your Shopify inventory automatically and keeps a record of exactly what came in.","k":"How to receive Partial and short receipts Costs update automatically Receiving history Related"},{"t":"Cycle counts & adjustments","u":"/docs/counts/cycle-counts-and-adjustments.html","s":"Counts","d":"Cycle counting is how you keep your inventory honest: physically count what's on the shelf, compare it to the system, and reconcile any difference back to Shopify. Stockwik makes t","k":"Running a count What happens on commit History Related"},{"t":"Transferring stock","u":"/docs/transfers/transferring-stock.html","s":"Transfers","d":"A transfer moves stock from one location to another — ship it from the source, receive it at the destination, and Stockwik keeps both locations' inventory accurate in Shopify along","k":"Creating a transfer Ship → receive → close Statuses Related"},{"t":"Reports overview","u":"/docs/reports/reports-overview.html","s":"Reports","d":"Reports turn your data into answers — what's tied up in stock, what's selling, how your suppliers perform, and what's moved. They're organized into four groups.","k":"Inventory & valuation Sales & profitability Purchasing & suppliers Operations & audit Common controls Related"},{"t":"Settings: Planning defaults","u":"/docs/settings/planning-defaults.html","s":"Settings","d":"Planning defaults are the store-wide settings behind your reorder suggestions and classifications. Set them once here; override individual products as needed.","k":"Settings Related"},{"t":"Settings: Company profile","u":"/docs/settings/company-profile.html","s":"Settings","d":"Your company profile is the business information that appears on the purchase orders you send to suppliers.","k":"Fields Where it shows up Related"},{"t":"Settings: Locations","u":"/docs/settings/locations.html","s":"Settings","d":"Your locations come from Shopify. Stockwik shows them here and lets you pick which one purchase orders deliver to by default.","k":"The locations list Default receiving location Multiple locations Related"},{"t":"Settings: Plan & billing","u":"/docs/settings/plan-and-billing.html","s":"Settings","d":"This is where you see your current plan and make changes. All billing runs through Shopify.","k":"What you'll see Actions Related"},{"t":"Plans & features","u":"/docs/account/plans-and-features.html","s":"Account & billing","d":"Stockwik has three plans. All include a 14-day free trial, and billing is handled through Shopify. The through-line: Starter tells you what to buy; Growth lets you act on it; Pro a","k":"At a glance Which plan is right? Related"},{"t":"Changing your plan","u":"/docs/account/changing-your-plan.html","s":"Account & billing","d":"You can upgrade or downgrade anytime. Plan changes go through Shopify, and new features unlock as soon as the change is confirmed.","k":"How to change plans Upgrades and downgrades Your trial Related"},{"t":"Workspace & team","u":"/docs/account/workspace-and-team.html","s":"Account & billing","d":"Your workspace is your Stockwik account. It's connected to one Shopify store and holds all your suppliers, buy options, purchase orders, counts, and settings.","k":"One store, one workspace Inviting your team Signing out Related"},{"t":"Reconnecting your store","u":"/docs/account/reconnecting-your-store.html","s":"Account & billing","d":"Occasionally Stockwik will ask you to reconnect your Shopify store. It's quick, and your data is safe — reconnecting just restores the secure link between Stockwik and Shopify.","k":"Two situations How to reconnect If it keeps happening Related"},{"t":"FAQ","u":"/docs/troubleshooting/faq.html","s":"Troubleshooting","d":"Quick answers to the questions merchants ask most.","k":"Why am I seeing \"Choose a plan to continue\"? Why is a feature locked (the 🔒)? Why is a product's reorder suggestion 0? Why did a reorder suggestion suddenly jump up? How far back does Stockwik look at sales? How often does Stockwik sync? Does Stockwik change my Shopify inventory? Can I connect more than one Shopify store? Related"},{"t":"Common issues","u":"/docs/troubleshooting/common-issues.html","s":"Troubleshooting","d":"Fixes for the handful of things that occasionally trip people up.","k":"My numbers look out of date \"Your store is disconnected\" / \"Reconnect your store\" My PO won't email A count line was rejected when I committed My import won't apply A feature shows a lock (🔒) I'm stuck on a full-screen message Related"}];
